; =============================================================================
; scripts.lst - Format Reference
; =============================================================================
;
; The real scripts.lst is embedded in master.dat and contains 1303 entries.
; You do NOT need to modify or create this file to use JavaScript scripts.
;
; The engine (Fallout 2 CE) automatically detects .js files placed in
; data\scripts\ and uses them instead of the compiled .int from master.dat.
; Just drop a .js file — no scripts.lst editing required.
;
; This file documents the FORMAT only, for advanced use cases.
;
; =============================================================================
; FORMAT
; =============================================================================
;
; Each non-empty, non-comment line is one script entry.
; Scripts are identified by ZERO-BASED LINE INDEX, not by name.
; Map files (.map) store a 1-based scriptIndex that maps directly here.
;
; Line format:
;
;   scriptname.int                         (compiled INT script)
;   scriptname.int  ; optional comment     (comment after filename)
;   scriptname.int  # local_vars=5         (local variable count metadata)
;   scriptname.int  ; comment  # local_vars=10   (both)
;
;   scriptname.js                          (JavaScript script — CE extension)
;   scriptname.js   # local_vars=0        (JS script with local var metadata)
;
; Parser rules:
;   - The engine looks for ".int" or ".js" substring to determine type.
;   - Everything after "#" on the same line is metadata.
;   - "local_vars=N" sets the number of local variables for the script.
;   - Lines starting with ";" are comments and are NOT parsed as script entries.
;     (Do not add comment-only lines in the real file — this shifts indices!)
;
; =============================================================================
; CRITICAL RULES
; =============================================================================
;
;   1. NEVER add or remove lines in the real scripts.lst.
;      Map files reference scripts by 1-based line number.
;      Adding/removing lines shifts ALL indices and breaks ALL maps.
;
;   2. The engine checks for a matching .js file on disk BEFORE loading .int.
;      So you can override any script just by placing a .js file in:
;        data\scripts\<scriptname>.js
;      You do NOT need to change scripts.lst at all.
;
;   3. If you do supply a custom scripts.lst in data\scripts\scripts.lst,
;      it MUST contain all 1303 entries in the correct order.
;      The VFS will use your file instead of the one in master.dat.
;
; =============================================================================
; TEMPLE OF TRIALS (ARTemple) — REAL INDEX
; =============================================================================
;
; The Temple of Trials map script is ARTemple, at LINE INDEX 744 (0-based).
; The map stores scriptIndex=745 (1-based).
;
; In the vanilla scripts.lst it looks like:
;
;   ARTemple.int    ; Arroyo Temple map script      # local_vars=0
;
; To override it with JavaScript, simply place your script at:
;
;   data\scripts\ARTemple.js
;
; The engine will auto-detect it and use it instead of ARTemple.int.
; No scripts.lst modification needed.
;
; =============================================================================
; EXAMPLE ENTRIES (illustrative — line numbers are for reference only)
; =============================================================================
;
; Line 0:
gloklint.int             # local_vars=0
; Line 1:
dcKlint.int              # local_vars=0
; Line 2:
acklint.int              # local_vars=10
; ...
; Line 744 (Temple of Trials):
ARTemple.int             # local_vars=0
; Line 745:
ARBridge.int             # local_vars=6
; ...
; (1303 entries total in the real file)
